I was worried that a @suppress tag would fail to warn about a legitimate redeclaration error:

for(var i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
	alert(i);
}

for(var i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
	alert(i);
}

However, that was not the case (the @suppress only applied to the first re-declaration). I've updated the codereview to just be an extern change.
